<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFWald.2C_Robert_M.1992"><a href="/wiki/Robert_Wald" title="Robert Wald">Wald, Robert M.</a> (1992), <i>Space, Time, and Gravity: The Theory of the Big Bang and Black Holes</i>, University of Chicago Press, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0226870294" class="internal">ISBN 0-226-87029-4</a></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Space%2C+Time%2C+and+Gravity%3A+The+Theory+of+the+Big+Bang+and+Black+Holes&amp;rft.aulast=Wald%2C+Robert+M.&amp;rft.au=Wald%2C+Robert+M.&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Chicago+Press&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Black_hole"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>
</ul>
<p><a name="Research_papers" id="Research_papers"></a></p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline">Research papers</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFHawking.2C_S.2005">Hawking, S. (2005). "Information loss in black holes". <i>Physical Review D</i> <b>72</b>: 084013. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103%2FPhysRevD.72.084013" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103%2FPhysRevD.72.084013" rel="nofollow">10.1103/PhysRevD.72.084013</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/ArXiv" title="ArXiv">arΧiv</a>:<a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-th/0507171v2" class="extiw" title="arxiv:hep-th/0507171v2">hep-th/0507171v2</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Information+loss+in+black+holes&amp;rft.jtitle=Physical+Review+D&amp;rft.aulast=Hawking%2C+S.&amp;rft.au=Hawking%2C+S.&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.volume=72&amp;rft.pages=084013&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1103%2FPhysRevD.72.084013&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Black_hole"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Stephen Hawking's purported solution to the black hole <a href="/wiki/Unitarity" title="Unitarity" class="mw-redirect">unitarity</a> paradox, first reported at a conference in July 2004.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFGhez.2C_A._M.2005">Ghez, A. M. (2005). "Stellar Orbits around the Galactic Center Black Hole". <i>The Astrophysical Journal</i> <b>620</b>: 744. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1086%2F427175" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1086%2F427175" rel="nofollow">10.1086/427175</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/ArXiv" title="ArXiv">arΧiv</a>:<a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/astro-ph/0306130v2" class="extiw" title="arxiv:astro-ph/0306130v2">astro-ph/0306130v2</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Stellar+Orbits+around+the+Galactic+Center+Black+Hole&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Astrophysical+Journal&amp;rft.aulast=Ghez%2C+A.+M.&amp;rft.au=Ghez%2C+A.+M.&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.volume=620&amp;rft.pages=744&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1086%2F427175&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Black_hole"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> More accurate mass and position for the black hole at the centre of the Milky Way.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFHughes2005">Hughes, Scott A. (2005). "Trust but verify: The case for astrophysical black holes".  <i><a href="/wiki/ArXiv" title="ArXiv">arΧiv</a>: <a href="http://www.arxiv.org/abs/hep-ph/0511217v2" class="external text" title="http://www.arxiv.org/abs/hep-ph/0511217v2" rel="nofollow">hep-ph/0511217v2</a></i> [hep-ph].</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Trust+but+verify%3A+The+case+for+astrophysical+black+holes&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Hughes&amp;rft.aufirst=Scott+A.&amp;rft.au=Hughes%2C+Scott+A.&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Black_hole"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Lecture notes from 2005 <a href="/wiki/SLAC" title="SLAC" class="mw-redirect">SLAC</a> Summer Institute.</li>
</ul>
